Terror-linked Minister, Pantami Had Poor Record Of Service As Abubakar Tafawa Balewa University Lecturer — Nigerian Lecturers’ Union, ASUU
0 Comments
7 Hours Ago





According to the report, the minister's CV and report establishing his prima facie alongside the external assessors' report were all hidden indicating a cover-up. The report stated, “There is no document indicating that Dr. Ibrahim was an expert in cyber security. His CV and the report establishing his prima facie case and the external assessors' report all remain hidden. This is an indication that something is being covered up.” Meanwhile, the report noted that only one person established prima facie for Pantami as opposed to the rules and regulations of the university. Also, ASUU argued further that Pantami was never qualified to be appointed as a professor, stressing that he doesn't “possess the leadership quality and experience expected of a professor who should be a mentor to others." Also, the report said Pantami never supervised or produced a PhD student and never held an administrative position in the university. It noted that even the PhD student assigned to him to co-supervise was done on the 9th September 2021 after his appointment as a professor. The report also noted that the minister did not meet the 12 years post qualification requirement in the advertisement as he only had one year of post PhD teaching experience. It added: “From available information, the publications of Dr Isa Ali Ibrahim did not go through similarity index (Turn-it-in), a condition that he was to meet. The turn-it-in process was established in 2018 and it has since been in use for every case of appointment and promotion in FUTO.”